ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Time Point
Trial type
Hour of the day of the sample
Change in acceleration in the X axis in m/s^2
Change in acceleration in the Y axis in m/s^2
Change in acceleration in the Z axis in m/s^2
Root mean square acceleration across al three axes in m/s^2 using: sqrt(X^2+Y^2+Z^2)
Description of reason for GPS sample
Notes: Activating = Phone turned on location services; App-Pausing = App switched to background; App-Resuming = App switched to foreground; Deactivating = Phone turned off location services; Disabling-Services = Location services turned off; Disabling-Timer = Location services turned off from timer; Enabling-Services = Location services turned on from timer; gps-Disabled = Location services turned off; Location-Changed = GPS coordinates changed since last recording; network-Disabled = Network location services turned off; Status-Changed = Satellite connection lost

ElementDescription: Location tracking turned on
Notes: TRUE = Location services on; FALSE = Location services off

ElementDescription: Type of location services available
Notes: network-and-gps = Network and GPS sattelites; network-only = Network; no-location-services = No location services

ElementDescription: Source of GPS location
Notes: gps = GPS system; network = cellular or wifi signal

ElementDescription: Accuracy of GPS coordinates in meters

For periodic tracking, current OFF duration

time of recording
Number of satelites used in recording
Change in distance in meters from previous recording

GPS location in degrees, masked with participant home equal to 0
